SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYTuesday 21 June S10 V2 It has been just weeks since Real Madrid won the Champions League but the next edition will get underway on Tuesday with a mini tournament in Iceland between the four lowest entrants in the 2022-23 field. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Slovakia U19 vs Italy U19: Slovakia’s under-19 side are hosting this group game against the Italians, who last won the European Championship at under-19 level in 2003.M2 Romania U19 vs France U19: Second match in three days for both teams in the Slovakian town of Dunajska Streda, which is hosting one of the European U-19 Championship groups.M3 IA Akranes vs FH: IA have collected a paltry seven points from their opening 10 games of the new season in Iceland. FH have eight points from as many games.M4 Valur Reykjavik vs Leiknir Reykjavik: After losing our games in a row, Valur brought an end to league leaders Breidablik’s 100% record with 3-2 win last Thursday. Leiknir have gone 10 games without a victory.M5 FCI Levadia vs Vikingur Reykjavik: The new Champions League campaign starts in Reykjavik with a mini tournament involving clubs from Iceland, Lithuania, San Marino and Andorra.M6 Aldosivi vs Platense: Aldosivi have lost their past five outings. Platense have started the new season in Argentina with seven points from three matches.M7 Chapecoense vs CRB: Chapecoense won away at Bahia in their last outing to end a run of seven matches without success. CRB have the same number of points as Chapecoense in the Brazil second division but played one game more.M8 Central Cordoba SdE vs San Lorenzo: Central Cordoba beat Boca Junior in their last home game but before that went seven home fixtures without a win. San Lorenzo have drawn their last four games in a row.M9 Suriname U20 vs Haiti U20: Group game in the Concacaf U-20 Championship, which is being hosted in Honduras.M10 Guatemala U20 vs Panama U20: The win count in previous clashes between the under-20 sides of Guatemala and Panama is 6-5 in favour of Panama with one draw. Suggested permutation:R4.00 3 x 3 x 3 x 1 x 3 x 3 x 1 x 1,2 x 1 x 3